29/06/2003
BUDAPEST, Hungary -- The prime ministers and top officials of Central and East European countries are attending a conference entitled "Roma in Enlarging Europe: Challenges for the Future". 
The two-day conference opened on Sunday (29 June). 
Participants will discuss a World Bank report on the Roma minorities in the region, focusing on their problems in Bulgaria, Hungary, Romania and Slovakia. 
The report also cites examples from the Czech Republic, Macedonia, Serbia-Montenegro and Spain. 
The conference is organised by the World Bank, George Soros' Open Society Institute and the European Commission. 
Representatives of Roma political organisations and NGOs in the region are also attending. 
(MIA - 29/06/03; BTA - 27/06/03)
